<item>
            <title>[DATAMONGO-553] StackOverflowError when objects have cycles</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-553</link>
                <project id="10701" key="DATAMONGO">Spring Data MongoDB</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The issue was first reported to Spring Integration project: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.springsource.org/browse/INT-2778&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://jira.springsource.org/browse/INT-2778&lt;/a&gt; and we narrowed down the problem to the fact that the persisted object had a cycle. In the reported case persisted object is Exception who&apos;s default &apos;cause&apos; is &apos;this&apos; thus creating a cycle.&lt;br/&gt;
I think classes of type Throwable needs to be treated in a special way where instead of using Reflection getCause() should be called.&lt;br/&gt;
However it would also help to have some cycle detection mechanism even for the purpose of throwing a more meaningful exception (e.g., Cycle detected)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
